Pre-heat your #oven{} to 220°C. Chop the @potatoes{450} into wedges the size
and width of your index finger (no need to peel). Grate the @mature cheddar
cheese{30%g}. Pop the wedges on a #baking tray{} lined with #baking paper{}. Drizzle
over some @olive oil{1.5%tbsp}, a pinch of @salt{} and @dried thyme{1/2%tsp}.
Put on the top shelf of your oven. Roast for ~{30-35%minutes}. After
~{25-30%minutes}, turn the wedges and sprinkle over the cheese. Roast for the
remaining ~{5%minutes}.

Trim the ends from the @cucumber{1/2}(trimmed and chopped into small pieces), quarter
lengthways then chop widthways into small pieces. Zest the @lime{1/2} and put the
zest to the side, then squeeze the lime juice into a #mixing bowl{} and add the
@honey{7.5%ml} and olive oil. Mix together and set aside. This is the salad
dressing! TIP: Don't dress the salad until just before serving or it will wilt.

Meanwhile, lay one of the @British chicken breasts{2} between two sheets of
#clingfilm{} and bash with either a #rolling pin{} or #frying pan{} until 2cm thick.
Repeat for all breasts. Cut each of the flattened breasts into six or seven long
strips.

Put a glug of @olive oil{} in a large frying pan on medium-high heat. Let it get
really hot. In the meantime, put the @plain flour{24%g} in another mixing bowl with
the lime zest, @paprika{3/4%tsp} and remaining dried thyme. Season with a really
good pinch of @salt{} and @pepper{}. Mix together then add the chicken strips.
Toss with your hands to ensure the chicken is well coated in the seasoned flour.
> IMPORTANT: Remember to wash your hands and equipment after handling raw meat.

Once the oil is hot, add half the chicken to the pan. Cook until golden all over,
~{3-4%minutes} on each side. Transfer to a baking tray covered in #kitchen paper{}
and cover loosely with #foil{}. Repeat with the remaining chicken. Once cooked,
sprinkle over some @salt{}. TIP: Cooking the chicken in batches helps prevent
overcrowding and makes for tastier, golden chicken!

Warm the chicken dippers through in your oven for a few mins if necessary. Add the
cucumber and @wild rocket{20} to the bowl of dressing and toss to combine.
Serve the chicken dippers with a dollop of @tomato ketchup{1}, some cheesy wedges
and some zesty salad. Enjoy!